track_notes: Through gate at public road end, parking SEEMED to be OK. Rough area to park. Follow track to house and R over FB. Veer left off main path up into woods. Complex route up through trees - follow map or GPS track carefully. Watch for turning at SH 7404 6119, easily missed. Some boggy sections. Once out of the woods at SH 7417 6200 head north, do not be tempted west along woods edge. No path higher up to reach ridge and there is a lot of deep heather. More boggy sections until you reach the ridge.
Space for one car at start. Ground can be boggy after heavy rainful. Easy walk to summit.

I parked just over Pontbrwynog on the access road to Llyn Cowlyd. You could drive a bit further but there was nowhere obvious to park. There are locked gates so you cannot go all the way to the dam.
At the south end of the dam is a warning / no trespassing sign next to a very inviting stile. It was not clear what to stay off, so my route runs well down-stream of the spill-way. There is no warning from the descent side.
Follow track up the hill, joining Geralds Llyn Crafnant track at SH742624.

Total time (including ops): 4hr 10m. Maximum difficulty: Swiss Alpine Club Grade T2. Uncurated GPX which may contain navigation errors, detours and hazards. Additional route information may be available at www.m1hax.uk. Track data by Richard M1HAX licensed under Creative Commons BY-NC-SA.
